  "description": "## T-0991 [ ] P3: Синхронизировать expected exit codes в audit manifest с evidence summaries\n\n- Создана: 2026-07-08T18:11:00+03:00\n- Состояние: open\n- Приоритет: P3\n- Execution class: `internal-substrate`\n- Scheduling tier: `later`\n- Зависимости: T-0990\n- Ссылки:\n  - Доменный документ: `docs/release-management/audit-package.md`\n  - Исходный код: `eng/Electron2D.Build/AuditPackageCommand.cs`\n  - Тесты: `tests/Electron2D.Tests.Integration/RepositoryBuildToolTests.cs`\n  - Источник follow-up: `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r05.md`\n\n### Execution contract\n\n- Task type: audit-tooling-hardening\n- Ready-to-start:\n  - task state is `open`.\n  - `docs/release-management/audit-package.md` describes the current audit manifest/evidence contract.\n  - a focused RED test can generate a package with one expected-success and one expected-failure preflight check.\n- Stop conditions:\n  - the change would alter saved external verdicts, manual ZIP assembly, browser submit behavior or current `T-0990` scope.\n  - expected-failure evidence would be hidden instead of represented consistently in `AUDIT-MANIFEST.md`.\n- May change:\n  - audit package manifest rendering and direct tests/docs.\n  - generated local documentation index after docs updates.\n  - task notes and diary for this task.\n- Must not change:\n  - public runtime API, API profile decisions or generated API class packets.\n  - saved audit reports.\n- Required outputs:\n  - `AUDIT-MANIFEST.md` preflight rows show the same expected exit code as corresponding `evidence/**/result.txt`.\n  - regression proving expected-failure checks are rendered consistently.\n- Required commands:\n  - focused audit package builder regression.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify audit-contracts`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify audit-followups`\n  - `git diff --check`\n- External audit:\n  - not required unless bundled with a parent audit-tooling package.\n\n### Самодостаточное описание\n\nr05 primary audit for `T-0990` found that `AUDIT-MANIFEST.md` listed expected exit code `0` for intentional failure checks, while each raw `result.txt` correctly recorded `expectedExitCode=1`, `actualExitCode=1`, `status=PASS`. The raw evidence was sufficient for `T-0990`, but the manifest should not contradict the evidence summaries.\n\n### Internal substrate acceptance contract\n\n- Audit manifest preflight rows must mirror expected exit codes from structured evidence summaries.\n- Expected-failure checks remain explicit and reviewable.\n- The fix is limited to audit package metadata/rendering and does not change task behavior or external verdict handling.\n\n### Критерии приёмки\n\n- [ ] Focused regression fails on mismatched manifest/evidence expected exit codes.\n- [ ] Audit package manifest renders expected-failure checks with the expected non-zero code.\n- [ ] Audit contract verifier and audit follow-up verifier pass.\n\n### Подзадачи\n\n- [ ] Add RED test for expected-failure manifest rendering.\n- [ ] Fix audit package manifest rendering.\n- [ ] Update `docs/release-management/audit-package.md` if the documented manifest contract changes.\n- [ ] Run focused checks, `verify audit-contracts`, `verify audit-followups` and `git diff --check`.\n\n### Current evidence\n\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r01.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F1\n  - state: tracked-new\n  - target: T-0991\n  - rationale: Primary audit r01 classified audit manifest expected exit code drift as P3 audit packaging hardening. Raw evidence for `T-0990` was correct, so this task tracks the manifest quality fix without expanding current `T-0990` scope.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r02.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F1\n  - state: tracked-new\n  - target: T-0991\n  - rationale: Primary audit r02 repeated the same manifest/evidence expected exit 